The paper proposes a novel method for unsupervised feature selection using autoencoders and group lasso regularization. This method is particularly useful for dealing with high-dimensional data in areas such as computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the proposed method involves neural networks, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with feature selection, which is a common problem in signal processing, cs.SI (Signal Processing) is also a possible sub-category.
